<br>
Necro:  Int to 200 (applies to all int casters), then just load up on the hit points.  This way you can transfer hp to mana and stay in decent shape for mana.  Also, some +med skill items help too (also applies to all casters).<br>
<br>
I don't know a ton about wizard, Chanters, and Mages but again, int to 200 and FT/Med items will help.  Also, each class has some very useful items you can pick up, like the Staff of the Temperate Flux, etc...<br>
<br>
As far as Shamen go:  Yes, they do Melee.  Not especially well, but much better than an int caster.  Also, their slows mean that they won't get completely eaten alive in combat.  However, as a Shamen I would want that tunic much more for the HPs than the fighting ability. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.primenightmare.org/gallery/kubie_sig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kaginos>Kaginos</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/11/03 8:42:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4113.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Flowing Fungi?</span><hr size=1> Earring of the Solstice has a level requirement, so that wouldn't work.  To answer your question about a similar caster item to a fungi tunic in regards to downtime for low level characters, the simple answer is &quot;no&quot;, unless you had access to really high-end FT items with no level requirement.<br>
<br>
Keric<br>
56 Myrmidon or Rallos Zek<br>
Firiona Vie <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thevolcanogod>thevolcanogod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 713<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/11/03 9:09:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4113.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Flowing Fungi?</span><hr size=1> Aye, you would have to spend well over 200K PP to twink an INT caster out with enough FT items to make a big difference (they are not easy to come by). I also believe Solstice Earring has a recommended level on it but the FT still works from level 1. This is what I was told way back when I got mine - not sure if it has changed or not so don’t take my word for it.<br>
<br>
With all of our problems, Shaman has got to be the most fun of any class I have played in EQ so far. If you choose that route you will find out what I am talking about – there is so much we can do and many people who just PL through to 50 don’t get to appreciate that. Fungi Tunic is a great item for Pre-55 Shaman – you will be able to canni down then regen up with the tunic. We don’t melee well but we can take a beating and a popular fighting tactic is to tank for our dog using DOTs and debuffs to hold agro. I wouldn’t try this in PoP tho <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
