<span class=title> Re: Flowing Fungi?</span><hr size=1> There are a few items for int casters that you can look for.  Zlandicar's Heart is great for any caster, but especially Necromancers, for the 5 points of regen.  I've seen quite a few for sale in the 35 to 50k range.  Velious robes for just about any int caster provide various nice effects, that all reduce downtime for a lowbie (any velious quest armor can be right-clicked at level 1).  I see the robes in the Bazaar all the time for 20 to 25k.<br>
<br>
You asked if FT 1 was anything like Breeze.  1 point of FT is equal to 1 point of mana regen per tick.  Most FT items give you the mana regen even before the recommended level.<br>
<br>
Playing a Shaman was the most fun I've had since I started playing, up until the raid stage.  Don't get me wrong, I love to raid, but for me, raid buffing sucks big time.  It's just not my cup of tea.  As a Shaman at 60 now, I can tell you there are some really fun things to solo.  Shaman are certainly not the only class that can do them, but it's been really exciting taking down things by myself  that I used to do in a raid setting.<br>
<br>
Now I've done everything I set out to do with my Shaman, so I'll move on to the next class.  (And no, I'm not selling <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   )  I had the most fun raiding with my Wizard, so I'll probably ride out the rest of my EQ time with him.<br>
